<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="assess-vt">assess <strong><em>vt</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /ə'ses/    美 /ə'ses/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>评价；评定</strong></h4>
<p>to make a judgment about a person or situation(judge)：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It’s difficult to <strong>assess the impact</strong> of the President’s speech. 
总统讲话产生的影响很难估计。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Many of the adults were assessed as having learning difficulties.
许多成年人被认定有学习困难。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>估算；估价</strong></h4>
<p>to calculate the value or cost of sth (estimate)：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Damage to the building was assessed at £40 000.
该建筑物的损失估定为4万英镑。</p></div></div>